title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1990-07-18

Set 1

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!, Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, Easy To Love You, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Morning Dew, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text:
Perhaps... Your weekend warrior received his reward?  My wife and I were dancing with friends on saidsame lawn.  A fellow matching your description repeatedly bounced into & stepped on her.  A friend, who had had a rather interesting ride from VA to IN and become hoarse, placed his hand around the person's neck - thumb under his chin, lifted him to eye/ear level and stated, "Be more careful of the lady next time.", and sent him hastily on his way as a projectile.

This was one of the best shows of the era.  Some would say that they should have ended with the Dew for effect.  The 2 night package and all the crazy Indiana Sh!t that went with it made for some powerful memories.  A great place to see shows for the veteran.  Mind the mobile courthouse etc.
